title: Turkey Tom
description: Tom and Jerry work together to save a live turkey from becoming the centerpiece of  a holiday feast.

title: Curiosity Thrilled the Cat
description: Tom and Jerry become obsessed with the contents of a wrapped package and go to extraordinary measure to find out what's inside without being caught by Rick and Ginger.

title: Pumpkin Punks
description: Maude tasks Tom with guarding her prize pumpkin until she enters it into competition at the county fair.

title: Scrunch Time
description: Tom's obsession with the sound his new crinkle ball drives the rest of the household crazy, forcing them to take drastic measures to rid the house of the annoying toy.

title: Always Say Never Again
description: Tom and Jerry are hired by a British super spy to help guard the Queen's precious objects while they are on display in the city.

title: I Dream of Jerry
description: A battle ensues over who will control the Genie that emerges from an antic lamp Ginger brings home from a yard sale.

title: Crazy for Ewe
description: A lost little lamb appears at Maude's farm.

title: Big Pig
description: A bet between two farmers over who can raise the biggest pig goes haywire for the farm hands.

title: Day of the Jackalope
description: On vacation in the west with Rick and Ginger, Tom and Jerry encounter the legendary Jackalope!

title: Dam Busters
description: Tom must cut fire word for the Manor fireplaces while Jerry harasses him.

title: Puppy Guard
description: An over protected Spike goes to extreme lengths to keep his precious pup safe from harm.

title: Pinata Yadda Yadda
description: Tom has trouble keeping track of a pinata full of stolen loot.

title: Hold the Cheese
description: To Tom and Jerry's delight, Ginger's new "no junk food in the house" diet causes Rick to sleep walk every night to the local fast food joint.

title: Hangin' Tough
description: Tom battles Butch to prove to Toodles that he's the better gentlemen.  While they battle it out, Jerry calls in Cousin Muscles who demonstrate how a true gentleman really behaves.

title: Mega-Tom
description: Frankenstein turns Tom into a colossus and Tom ends up terrorizing the village mice until Jerry Van Mouseling saves the day.

title: Play Date with Destiny
description: A wild chase leads Jerry into the arms of a little girl and now Tom has to help Jerry escape her clutches.

title: Something to Crow About
description: A scarecrow terrorizes Catsylvania.

title: Cave Cat
description: A prehistoric Cave Cat arrives at Rick and Ginger's House.

title: Shadow of a Doubt
description: The detectives are desperately trying to help George and Junior find a missing black panther from the city zoo.

title: Me and My Big Foot
description: A trip to the woods leads to an unexpected encounter with Big Foot.

title: Tom Prix
description: Tom, forced into driving a race car created by evil Dr. Otto, terrorizes the village mice until Jerry Van Mouseling comes to their rescue.

title: Un-Easy Chair
description: Tom must enlist the neighborhood cats to help him remove the cat hairs from Rick's new massage chair.

title: Tuxedo Junction
description: Quacker's cousin, and penguin named Tux, makes life miserable for Tom and Jerry when he insists on trying to devour the fish in Rick's new aquarium.

title: Mouse Party
description: Rick and Ginger leave town with instructions for Tom to keep the house in order, but Jerry's got other ideas.

title: Wild Goose Chase
description: The detectives agree to escort a goofy Canadian goose back across the border before duck hunting season begins.

title: Diamonds are for Never
description: The cat and mouse detectives are hired to find a missing rare diamond.

title: Downsizing
description: The gang are determined to make Rick and Ginger change their mind about downsizing and moving to the big city by making it impossible to sell the house.

title: Disappearing Tom
description: Tom is tricked into believing he is invisible.

title: The Three Little Mice
description: Papa tells his fractured version of the three Little Pigs story to the Bavarian mouse trio.

title: (Not) Your Father's Mouse-Stache
description: It's the battle of the moustaches when Tom accidentally drinks a hair tonic potion left behind by Jerry and Butch realizes he needs to acquire some facial hair of his own if he is to compete for Toodles and Dollface's attentions.

title: A Rare Breed
description: Jerry is mistaken for a rare breed of Guinea Pig by the Duchess' professor friend and uses his protected, elevated status to create endless problems for Tom.

title: A Kick in the Tail
description: When Tuffy shows an interest in soccer, Jerry decides to be the little guys coach and show him how the game is really played by beating Tom in a one-on-one match.

title: Counting Sheep
description: Tom and Jerry are hired by Dixie Wolf to find all the sheep that have gone missing.

title: All That Glitters
description: The cat and mouse detectives pose as bellhops at a swanky hotel to catch a jewel thief.

title: Dry Hard
description: A stranger with a diving rod promises to find water for the farm.

title: The Maltese Pigeon
description: Tom and Jerry are hired to find a missing priceless Maltese Pigeon.

title: Junkyard Pup
description: When Tyke is accidentally carried off to the local dump, Spike is forced to enlist the help of Jerry and Tom to get his boy back before Ace and Rocco, the junkyards guard dogs, turn him into a formidable junkyard pup.

title: Balloonatics
description: Tom and Jerry fight each other with the balloons that Rick has placed all over the house to surprise Ginger on their anniversary.

title: Ball of Fire
description: The hot dog relish that Crooked Eddie brings to the detectives turns out to be an explosive device that Tom and Jerry must now return to the lab before it inadvertently blows up the entire city.

title: Bones of Contention
description: Spikes bones are missing and Frankie the Rat is the culprit.  Now all they have to do is catch in the dirty rat in the act.

title: Oh Brother
description: Spike's big brother, Max, shows up on the run from some bad guys and Spike must enlist the help of Tuffy, Tom and Jerry to get rid of him.

title: A Treehouse Divided
description: From the security of his treehouse, Tom wages battle with Spike and Jerry.

title: Professor Meathead
description: Meathead turns into a genius when he gulps down a bottle of specially formulated water.

title: Donut Daze
description: It's a battle royale over the last box of donuts.

title: Farmed and Dangerous
description: Things get crazy down on the farm when a cat and mouse pursuit leads Jerry to hide his turtle egg in a hen's nest.

title: Party Animals
description: Tom is placed in charge of the preparations for the Duchess' surprise birthday party for nephew Rupert and Jerry is determined to make a mess of it all.

title: Who Sled the Dogs Out?
description: The detectives help a team of Huskies find the villain who is determined to sabotage their dog sled race.

title: The French Mistake
description: Tom is placed in charge of caring for the Duchess' French Poodle and needs Tuffy and Jerry's help in keeping the ill-tempered mutt under control.

title: What About Blob?
description: Tom turns into a Blob monster and proceeds to eat everything in sight, including the village mice!  Jerry Van Mouseling to the rescue!

title: Hip Replacement
description: The neighbor's cat turns out to be a hipster who's laid back attitudes and behaviors are soon adopted by Tom and the other alley cats. Annoyed, Jerry decides to put an end to all of their silly nonsense.

title: Tommy Appleseed
description: A Tom and Jerry take on the Johnny Appleseed story.

title: Un-Welcome Home
description: After taking the heat again from Ginger for Jerry's shenanigans, fed up Tom decides to pack his bags and go home to his birth family. But can you ever really go home again?

title: Jabberwock
description: Tom finds himself trapped inside a Catsylvania bedtime story and fleeing from a furious Jabberwock.

title: Pranks for Nothin'
description: It's the battle of the soldier angels when pranks run amok on April Fool's Day.

title: How to Be a Dog
description: Spike demonstrates for Tuffy what it takes to be a dog.

title: Polar Excess
description: Tom and Jerry have to contend with a baby polar bear that has been mistakenly delivered to Rick and Ginger's house.

title: Hot Wings
description: A lemur belonging to the Duchess' adventurous cousin puts Tom's job as Under-Butler in jeopardy.

title: Grumpelstiltskin
description: An oompah land retelling of the Rumplestiltskein story.

title: A Clown Without Pity
description: An evil ringmaster recruits Tom to help him snare the Catsylvania mice.

title: Chutes and Tatters
description: Tom's assigned laundry duty at the estate and Jerry's determined to soil the job.

title: The Not So Ugly Duckling
description: A couple of tricksters use Lil Quacker as their "magnificent" side show act in order to bilk the locals out of their cash.

title: Sock It to Me
description: There has been a wave of sock thefts from the local laundromat and the Cat and Mouse Detectives have been hired by Pontius Pig to solve the case before his laundry business goes belly up.

title: The Wearing of the Green
description: Jerry helps a Leprechaun retrieve the pot of gold that he's lost to Tom.

title: Officer Tyke
description: Tyke undergoes a personality change after watching too many cop shows on TV.

title: Three Heads Are Better Than One
description: Tom, Jerry Van Mouseling and the village mice must deal with a howling three head dog that Tom has accidentally awakened.

title: Cat-astrophic Failure
description: Spike leaves Tom in charge of his boy Tyke only to discover upon his return that Tyke now behaves more like a cat than a dog.

title: A Kick in the Butler
description: A Tom and Jerry chase through Postlewaite Manor results in major injuries to Cates which places his defense of the Butler's Linen Gloves Boxing Title in jeopardy. But never fear, Tom will step into the ring and defend Cate's title.

title: Hush Puppy
description: Ginger is asked by her mother to watch her dog, Goliath, while she is away. Goliath is a gentle giant, unless you wake him from his nap!

title: Tom's Cruise
description: Tom and Jerry get locked inside a travel trunk and end up on a vacation cruise to France.

title: My Buddy Guard
description: A robot turns from friend to foe forcing Tom, Jerry, Spike and Tuffy to team up in order to rid themselves of the invader.

title: Rikki Tikki Tabby
description: The Duke returns from India with some wild animals that escape their cages and begin to terrorize the manor. Tom is tasked with putting everything back in order.

title: The Ol' Switcheroo
description: Tuffy's wish to be as strong as Spike comes true.

title: Para-Abnormal Activities
description: Jerry pretends to be a ghost to terrorize Tom until he gets a fright of his own.

title: Duck Sitting
description: Tom and Jerry must keep Lil' Quacker safe from Butch and Meathead so that he can testify to a crime in court.

title: Millennium Mouse
description: An ancient flying machine is discovered in Postlewaite Manor.

title: Yeti, Set, Go
description: When Tom inadvertently set a Yeti loose on the town, Jerry Van Mouseling must subdue the beast.

title: Cat-A-Combs
description: Tom falls into a manhole and finds a magic cloak that turns him into King of the Catacombs.

title: Mind Your Royal Manners
description: Fearful that he will lose his place in the Manor, Tom adopts the attitude of a member of the Royal Guard in order to keep the mice and their new friend, Boswell, from wreaking havoc in the kitchen.

title: The Old Gray Hair
description: After discovering a gray hair, Spikes decides he's too old to be the alpha of the house which sends Tom into full bully mode. Jerry will have to act fast to convince Spike he's still the alpha dog.

title: The Masked Mouse
description: Tuffy surprises Jerry with a visit from the actor who plays his favorite TV show character, "The Masked Mouse". Turns out, the actor is a prima donna who makes everyone's life miserable.

title: Camelot Cat
description: Tom and Jerry save King Arthur's kingdom from an evil sorcerer, Morgan.

title: Ball of Fame
description: When Tom and Jerry's antics unearth an autographed baseball, a childhood souvenir of Rick's, he warns Tom to keep his paws off it, or else! Tom attempts to obey but Jerry's got other ideas and the ball gets out of hand. The guys chase the treasured ball all over the neighborhood, recovering it only to lose it again and again.

title: Doghouse Rock
description: Tom is mistakenly placed in a shelter for homeless animals and forced to join the shelter's rock-n-roll while Jerry lives the life of Riley back home.

title: Tap Cat
description: An old pair of Ginger's tap shoes turns Tom into a tap dancing fanatic.

title: Tom Thumblestein
description: Papa tells his fractured version of the Tom Thumb story to the Bavarian mouse trio.

title: Flower Power
description: A bouquet of flowers causes Tom no end of trouble.

title: Tick Tick Tick
description: Jerry uses a friendly tick to get even with Tom.

title: The Butterfly Effect
description: Tuffy and Jerry, pretending to be butterflies, prank Tom and cause all sorts of trouble in the house until the Duke catches Tuffy with the intention of adding him to his butterfly collection.

title: Ten Toms the Trouble
description: Tom uses a new fangled scientific machine to make copies off himself creating a living nightmare for Jerry.

title: See Ya Gator
description: Jerry befriends a lost baby gator, keeping it safe from harm until it's momma arrives to take it back home.

title: Broom for Improvement
description: The gang do battle with a magical broom.

title: It's the Little Things
description: When Tom drinks a potion given to him by a Gypsy woman and shrinks to the size of an insect, he must beg Jerry Van Mouseling for help in finding a cure.

title: The Great Catsby
description: Tom must compete with his American cousin for the right to remain a Butler at Postlewaite manor.

title: Eight Legs No Waiting
description: The gang get more than they bargained for when they try to shoo away a seemingly docile spider.

title: Downton Crabby
description: Jerry battles Tom to save a crab from becoming the Duke and Duchess' main course.

title: Maust
description: Tom is tricked into helping an evil magician capture all of the mice in the village, but Jerry Van Mouseling foils the magician's plans.

title: Little Red Katzen Hood
description: Tom is off to visit his grandma with a basket of goodies when he encounters a Wolf and a Witch on the same path to Grandma's house.

title: The Devil You Know
description: A guilty conscience causes Butch to change his ways. But Tom, Jerry, Spike and Tuffy quickly decide they like the old Butch better.

title: Giant Problems
description: Papa tells his fractured version of the Jack and the Beanstalk story to the Bavarian mouse trio.

title: Mr. Nobody
description: The Cat and Mouse detectives are hired to track down Tuffy's imaginary scapegoat, Mr. Nobody.

title: Tom Save the Queen
description: The detectives across the hall are responsible for a series of high profile thefts and are framing innocent people for the crimes.

title: Attachment Disorder
description: Tom and Spike get glued together.

title: Slam Dunk
description: The Cat and Mouse are hired to find out who absconded with Hoops McJumpalot's lucky high top sneakers.

title: Ghoul's Gold
description: Tom serves an evil pirate determined to steal treasure belonging to the village mice until Jerry Van Mouseling foils his plans.

title: Tom Quixote
description: A knock on the head turns Tom into Quixote that leads him into battle with Butch over Toodles affections.

title: Lord Spike
description: A lineage check determines that Spike is descended from British aristocracy.

title: Top Dog
description: The gang get more than they bargained for when the dog next door shows up.

title: Gym Rat
description: Overweight Jerry starts working out on a weight machine supplied to him by cousin Muscles. Not to be oudone, Tom starts lifting weights as well, which sets up an epic battle royale between the cat and mouse.

title: Dog Star Spike
description: The Mice from Mars make a return visit and set about making mischief between Spike and Tom.

title: Werewolf of Catsylvania
description: A werewolf terrorizes Tom and the inhabitants of the  Catsylvania village.

title: Into the Woods
description: When an accident leaves Jerry wrapped head to toe in bandages and unable to take his scout troop camping, a guilt-ridden Tom decides to lead the kids into the woods himself.

title: Not So Grand Canyon
description: Tom and Jerry take the scouts on a camping trip to canyon country and get more than they bargain for when a coyote pup shows up.

title: Loch Ness Mess
description: Tom enlists the help of the lake monster to terrorize the mouse village forcing Jerry Van Mouseling to intervene and save the day.

title: A Class of Their Own
description: Tom and Jerry are forced to go back to Detective School in order to renew their detective licenses.

title: Ape for Tom and Jerry
description: When Rick and Ginger forget Tom's birthday, the tomcat moves in with the one person who appreciates him, the local Zoo's gorilla, Cuddles.

title: Mice Fair Ladies
description: Jerry's cousins pay a return visit to the Manor eager to create mayhem for Tom, things get crazier than ever when the cousins wives show up as well.

title: Mice from Mars
description: Mice visitors from Mars force Tom to change the way he treats Jerry.
